"Boycott" Addon

Use cases:  
    One company can have multiple 'domains' values (array)
    One company can have multiple tags (array)
    There can be multiple causes (array)

If the user visits a domain and the pattern matches, a message is displayed across the top of the page simlar to:

<div>
<div left>Boycott: {causeViolation}<br>Company: <a href="{companyWikipedia}">{companyName}</a></div>
<div right hover={causeDescription}>{causeTitle}</div>
</div>

If there are 2 or more causes associated with a domain pattern, each causeViolation is presented

<div>
<div left>Boycott: <span class="bold">Multiple Violations</span><br>{causeViolation[0]}<br>{causeViolation[1]}<br>Company: <a href="{companyWikipedia}">{companyName}</a></div>
<div right hover={causeDescription}>{causeTitle}</div>
</div>

Example of JSON input 

{
    "company": [
        {
            "companyId": 0,
            "companyName": "Boycott Project",
            "companywikipedia": "https://secure.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/wiki/Boycott",
            "domains": [
                {
                    "pattern": "(*.boycott.com)"
                }
            ],
            "causes": [
                101
            ]
        }
    ],
    "causes": [
        {
            "causeId": 101,
            "causeTitle": "Bad",
            "causeDescription": "This cause is dedicated to examining things that are bad.  If you don't like bad things, support this cause.",
            "causeViolation": "This site promoted something bad.",
            "causeViolationEvidence": "Urls to supplimental material"
        }
    ]
}
